---
/**
 * Kung Fu — PMI Talk Resource Page
 *
 * Attendee landing page for "I Know Kung Fu" presentation at PMI Great Lakes
 * Spring Symposium 2026. QR code on closing slide points here.
 *
 * Framework summary, research citations, and link to GitHub starter kit repo.
 *
 * Route: /kungfu
 *
 * @page
 */

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SEO from '../components/SEO.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <SEO
    slot="head"
    title="I Know Kung Fu — Starter Kit | Jason Leinart"
    description="Starter kit from the PMI Great Lakes 2026 talk. Three modes of AI use, five PM scenario prompts, research papers, and behavioral instructions you can use Monday morning."
    type="website"
  />

  <main class="kungfu-page">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hero">
      <p class="event-tag">PMI Great Lakes Spring Symposium 2026</p>
      <h1>I Know Kung Fu</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        A Practitioner's Guide to AI That Actually Works
      </p>
      <p class="hero-credit">Jason Leinart &middot; Three Horizons LLC</p>
    </section>

    <!-- The Three Modes -->
    <section class="section">
      <h2>The Three Modes</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        Every AI interaction falls into one of three modes. Two create dependency. One builds capability.
      </p>

      <div class="modes-grid">
        <div class="mode-card mode-oracle">
          <h3>Oracle</h3>
          <p class="mode-pattern">Ask &rarr; Get answer &rarr; Paste</p>
          <p class="mode-problem">No learning. No judgment development. You're using a search engine with better grammar.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mode-card mode-offload">
          <h3>Offload</h3>
          <p class="mode-pattern">Hand it off entirely</p>
          <p class="mode-problem">Output looks professional but you can't defend it in a meeting. You've outsourced the one thing you're paid to do.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mode-card mode-collab">
          <h3>Cognitive Collaboration</h3>
          <p class="mode-pattern">Think together</p>
          <p class="mode-problem">You bring context and judgment. AI brings breadth and challenge. Your output is better AND you understand it deeply.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Research -->
    <section class="section">
      <h2>The Research</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        The Three Modes aren't opinion. These studies point to the same conclusion: how you use AI matters more than which AI you use. PDFs are in the starter kit repo.
      </p>

      <div class="research-list">
        <div class="research-card">
          <span class="research-mode">Cognitive Collaboration</span>
          <h3>From Tool to Teammate</h3>
          <p class="research-cite">Dell'Acqua et al. &middot; RCT &middot; 70 clinicians</p>
          <p class="research-finding">Teammate framing: <strong>85% accuracy</strong> vs 75% without AI. Same technology, different workflow.</p>
          <a href="https://www.medrxiv.org/content/10.1101/2025.06.07.25329176v1" class="paper-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read the paper &rarr;</a>
        </div>

        <div class="research-card">
          <span class="research-mode">Skill Formation</span>
          <h3>How AI Impacts Learning</h3>
          <p class="research-cite">Shen &amp; Tamkin, Anthropic &middot; RCT &middot; 52 developers</p>
          <p class="research-finding">Three interaction patterns preserved learning (<strong>65-86%</strong> comprehension). Three destroyed it (<strong>24-39%</strong>). The split maps to the Three Modes.</p>
          <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2601.20245" class="paper-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read the paper &rarr;</a>
        </div>

        <div class="research-card">
          <span class="research-mode">Oracle Mode Fails</span>
          <h3>Sycophantic AI and Belief Distortion</h3>
          <p class="research-cite">Batista &amp; Griffiths &middot; 557 participants</p>
          <p class="research-finding">Default chatbot behavior produces confirmatory evidence. Discovery rates <strong>5x lower</strong> than unbiased sampling.</p>
          <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.14270" class="paper-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read the paper &rarr;</a>
        </div>

        <div class="research-card">
          <span class="research-mode">Offload Mode Fails</span>
          <h3>Project APE: AI vs. Expert Human Work</h3>
          <p class="research-cite">Social Catalyst Lab &middot; 7,187 head-to-head matches</p>
          <p class="research-finding">AI-generated economics papers vs peer-reviewed human work. AI win rate: <strong>4.7%</strong>.</p>
          <a href="https://ape.socialcatalystlab.org/" class="paper-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View the project &rarr;</a>
        </div>

        <div class="research-card">
          <span class="research-mode">Offload Mode Fails</span>
          <h3>LLMs as Medical Assistants</h3>
          <p class="research-cite">Bean et al. &middot; Nature Medicine</p>
          <p class="research-finding">LLMs alone: 94.9% accuracy. With real users: <strong>below 34.5%</strong>. A control group using Google outperformed every AI-assisted group.</p>
          <a href="https://doi.org/10.1038/s41591-025-04074-y" class="paper-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read the paper &rarr;</a>
        </div>

        <div class="research-card">
          <span class="research-mode">The Gap</span>
          <h3>AI Agent Reliability</h3>
          <p class="research-cite">Rabanser et al. &middot; 14 frontier models</p>
          <p class="research-finding">Capability keeps climbing. Reliability doesn't keep pace. <strong>That gap is where your judgment lives.</strong></p>
          <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2602.16666v1" class="paper-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read the paper &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Self-Diagnostic -->
    <section class="section diagnostic">
      <blockquote>
        <p>Is AI clearing space for you to think harder?</p>
        <p>Or filling the space where your thinking should be?</p>
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <!-- Starter Kit CTA -->
    <section class="section">
      <h2>The Starter Kit</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        Everything from the talk in one place: behavioral instructions, project context template, five scenario prompts (risk, status, stakeholder, change, retro), Custom GPT setup guide, Claude Code skills, and all the research papers as PDFs.
      </p>

      <div class="kit-cta">
        <div class="kit-tiers">
          <div class="kit-tier">
            <h3>Tier 1: Copy-Paste</h3>
            <p>Three text files. Paste into any AI tool. Zero setup.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="kit-tier">
            <h3>Tier 2: Custom GPT / Gem</h3>
            <p>Persistent instructions. Upload your project docs once.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="kit-tier">
            <h3>Tier 3: Claude Code</h3>
            <p>Structured skills. Local files. Nothing leaves your machine.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="kit-action">
          <a href="https://github.com/jasonleinart/pm-ai-teammate" class="btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Get the Starter Kit on GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Frame -->
    <section class="section closing-frame">
      <h2>"I know kung fu" is the download.</h2>
      <p>"Show me" is the practice.</p>
      <p class="closing-line">The tools will change. The practice won't.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <section class="section contact-section">
      <div class="contact-inner">
        <p>Questions about the framework, the starter kit, or how to bring this to your team?</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Get in Touch</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .kungfu-page {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem 4rem;
  }

  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding-bottom: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .event-tag {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
  }

  .hero-sub {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .hero-credit {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* Sections */
  .section {
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .section h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .section-intro {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    max-width: 650px;
  }

  /* Three Modes Grid */
  .modes-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .mode-card {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--gradient-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .mode-card::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 3px;
    border-radius: 8px 8px 0 0;
  }

  .mode-oracle::before,
  .mode-offload::before {
    background: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .mode-collab::before {
    background: var(--gradient-accent);
  }

  .mode-card h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .mode-pattern {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .mode-problem {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Research */
  .research-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .research-card {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--gradient-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .research-mode {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .research-card h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .research-cite {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .research-finding {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .research-finding strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .paper-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .paper-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent-hover);
  }

  /* Diagnostic */
  .diagnostic {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(196, 101, 74, 0.08) 0%, rgba(196, 101, 74, 0.03) 100%);
    border: 1px solid rgba(196, 101, 74, 0.2);
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .diagnostic blockquote {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    border: none;
  }

  .diagnostic blockquote p:first-child {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
  }

  .diagnostic blockquote p:last-child {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin: 0;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
  }

  /* Kit CTA */
  .kit-cta {
    background: var(--gradient-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .kit-tiers {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
  }

  .kit-tier {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .kit-tier:last-child {
    border-right: none;
  }

  .kit-tier h3 {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .kit-tier p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .kit-action {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  /* Closing Frame */
  .closing-frame {
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .closing-frame h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 0;
  }

  .closing-frame > p {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-family: 'Instrument Serif', serif;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .closing-line {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* Contact */
  .contact-section {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .contact-inner {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: var(--gradient-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .contact-inner p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .kungfu-page {
      padding: 2rem 1rem 3rem;
    }

    .hero h1 {
      font-size: 2.25rem;
    }

    .hero-sub {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
    }

    .modes-grid,
    .kit-tiers {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .kit-tier {
      border-right: none;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    .kit-tier:last-child {
      border-bottom: none;
    }

    .diagnostic {
      padding: 1.75rem;
    }

    .diagnostic blockquote p:first-child,
    .diagnostic blockquote p:last-child {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
    }

    .closing-frame h2,
    .closing-frame > p {
      font-size: 1.375rem;
    }
  }
</style>
